You are implementing task #3 (PABLO-D-104.7) on the pablo-companion project.

## Your task
Create a ModelManager service that manages Whisper model files for local transcription.

## What to build

Create `mac/PabloCompanion/Services/ModelManager.swift`.

### QualityPreset enum
```swift
enum QualityPreset: String, CaseIterable, Sendable {
    case fast           // whisper-small (~200 MB)
    case balanced       // whisper-large-v3-turbo Q5_0 (~1.0 GB) — default
    case highAccuracy   // whisper-large-v3 (~1.6 GB) — on-demand download

    var modelFileName: String {
        switch self {
        case .fast: return "ggml-small.bin"
        case .balanced: return "ggml-large-v3-turbo-q5_0.bin"
        case .highAccuracy: return "ggml-large-v3.bin"
        }
    }

    var displayName: String { ... }
    var diskSizeDescription: String { ... }  // e.g. "~200 MB"
}
```

### ModelManager service
```swift
@MainActor
final class ModelManager: ObservableObject {
    static let shared = ModelManager()

    // ~/Library/Application Support/PabloCompanion/Models/
    private var modelsDirectory: URL { ... }

    /// Returns the path to the model file for the given preset.
    /// Checks modelsDirectory first, then app bundle.
    /// Throws ModelError.notFound if neither location has the file.
    func modelURL(for preset: QualityPreset) throws -> URL

    /// Whether the model for this preset is available (cached or bundled).
    func isAvailable(_ preset: QualityPreset) -> Bool

    /// Stub — throws ModelError.notImplemented.
    /// Future: download from Pablo CDN.
    func downloadModel(_ preset: QualityPreset) async throws
}

enum ModelError: Error, LocalizedError {
    case notFound(QualityPreset)
    case notImplemented
}
```

## Design notes
- `modelURL(for:)` checks `modelsDirectory/modelFileName` first, then `Bundle.main.url(forResource:withExtension:)`
- Create `modelsDirectory` with `withIntermediateDirectories: true` if it doesn't exist
- `isAvailable` calls `modelURL` and returns true if it doesn't throw
- No actual model files are bundled yet — that's fine, the service just resolves paths correctly. Tests will verify the logic with a temp directory.

## Rules
- Read the existing Services/ files first to match style (look at RecordingService.swift for patterns)
- Create branch: `git checkout -b PABLO-D-104.7-model-manager`
- After writing the file, run: `swiftlint lint --strict --config mac/.swiftlint.yml mac/PabloCompanion/` and fix any issues
- Run: `swiftformat --config mac/.swiftformat mac/PabloCompanion/`
- Commit: `feat: Add ModelManager service with QualityPreset enum`
- No Co-Authored-By lines in commits
- When done, mark task #3 as completed via TaskUpdate and message the team lead

## Project structure note
The project uses `PBXFileSystemSynchronizedRootGroup` (Xcode 16+) — new Swift files placed under `mac/PabloCompanion/` are automatically included automatically. No need to edit `.pbxproj`.

## SwiftLint notes
- Types with only static members must be `enum`, not `struct`  
- Always use `Color.pabloSage` fully qualified in `foregroundStyle()`/`fill()` calls
- `convenience_type`: if a class/struct has only static members, make it an enum

