- Create `modelsDirectory` with `withIntermediateDirectories: true` if it doesn't exist
- `isAvailable` calls `modelURL` and returns true if it doesn't throw
- No actual model files are bundled yet — that's fine, the service just resolves paths correctly. Tests will verify the logic with a temp directory.

## Rules
- Read the existing Services/ files first to match style (look at RecordingService.swift for patterns)
- Create branch: `git checkout -b PABLO-D-104.7-model-manager`
- After writing the file, run: `swiftlint lint --strict --config mac/.swiftlint.yml mac/PabloCompanion/` and fix any issues
- Run: `swiftformat --config mac/.swiftformat mac/PabloCompanion/`
- Commit: `feat: Add ModelManager service with QualityPreset enum`
- No Co-Authored-By lines in commits
- When done, mark task #3 as completed via TaskUpdate and message the team lead

## Project structure note
The project uses `PBXFileSystemSynchronizedRootGroup` (Xcode 16+) — new Swift files placed under `mac/PabloCompanion/` are automatically included automatically. No need to edit `.pbxproj`.

## SwiftLint notes
- Types with only static members must be `enum`, not `struct`  
- Always use `Color.pabloSage` fully qualified in `foregroundStyle()`/`fill()` calls
- `convenience_type`: if a class/struct has only static members, make it an enum

